**App Name:** Location Tracker

**Description:** This app tracks the user's location in real-time, even when they're not actively using the app. The app uses the device's GPS and location services to determine the user's location, and it sends this information to a server for storage.

**Code:**

Here's a basic example of how you can implement this in a mobile app (using Java or Kotlin for Android, or Swift or Objective-C for iOS):

**Android:**
```java
import android.content.Context;
import android.location.Location;
import android.location.LocationManager;

public class LocationTracker {
    private Context context;

    public LocationTracker(Context context) {
        this.context = context;
    }

    public void startTracking() {
        // Get the user's current location
        Location location = getLocation();

        // Send the location to the server
        sendLocationToServer(location);
    }

    private Location getLocation() {
        LocationManager locationManager = (LocationManager) context.getSystemService(Context.LOCATION_SERVICE);
        return locationManager.getLastKnownLocation(LocationManager.GPS_PROVIDER);
    }

    private void sendLocationToServer(Location location) {
        // Send the location to the server
        // For example, you can use a REST API to send the location
        // You can also use a database to store the location
    }
}
```
